de.dfki.embots.behaviorbuilder.model
Class PoseModel

java.lang.Object
  de.dfki.embots.embrscript.EMBRPose
      de.dfki.embots.behaviorbuilder.model.PoseModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
BBConstants, EMBRElement, java.lang.Comparable<PoseModel>
public class PoseModel
extends EMBRPose
implements java.lang.Comparable<PoseModel>, BBConstants

Internal pose representation, an extension of an EMBRPose, to be used in the EMBR-Poser's control panel and pose sequence table. Builds the pose sequence sent to the agent on-the-fly. Class encapsulates (aggregates) a EMBRPoseSequence to enrich it by additional attributes such as "enabled" (used in the later sequence), and an ID.

toSendableSequenceScript

public java.lang.String toSendableSequenceScript(java.lang.String agentCharacter)
Create an EMBRScript in string form that contains only this pose. Used e.g. by the "assume pose" facility. This method is intended for packaging a pose to be sent to the agent. There is probably no way to recycle the sendable script otherwise (note the tweaked timings).

Parameters:
agentCharacter - to whom it shall concern
Returns:
the generated one-pose-script

compareTo

public int compareTo(PoseModel other)
Compare this pose to another one. Poses are ordered by start time. However, two poses are considered equal only if they share the same id (in which case they also are references to the same PoseModel objects. Used for sorting in the sequence table, and for retrieving or deleting poses in the PoseSequence pose array.

Specified by:
